    index: 5,
    text: `The city wakes inside a locked drawer of light.
Somewhere, a hinge remembers the shape of opening.

I carry a small aquarium of weather in my chest—
its fish made of unfinished mornings.

They turn slowly through the glass of silence,
silver as rumors beneath ice.

Yesterday nailed its notices to the wind,
but the nails keep loosening.

In the alley of abandoned clocks
a thin green sound begins climbing the brick.

No one names it.
Still, the air practices breathing around it.`,
